# TypeScript & React

## Components

- Functional components only; use `import * as React from "react"`
- Export named functions: `export function HeroCard() { ... }`
- Type props with explicit interfaces or inline object types — never `any`
- Use `type` imports for types: `import type { Hero } from "@/types/domain"`

## Class names

Always merge conditional classes with `cn()`:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<div className={cn("rounded-xl border", isActive && "border-brand-gold")} />

// ❌ BAD — string concatenation
<div className={"rounded-xl " + (isActive ? "border-brand-gold" : "")} />
```

## Hooks

- Custom hooks live in `src/hooks/` with `use` prefix
- Derive filtered/sorted lists with `React.useMemo`
- Side effects (title, meta, storage) in `React.useEffect`

## State access

- Game/content data: `useAppStore()` from `@/contexts/DataContext`
- Auth: `useAuth()` from `@/contexts/AuthContext`
- Do not duplicate persisted state in page-level localStorage

## File naming

- Pages: `PascalCase` + `Page` suffix (`HeroesPage.tsx`)
- Components: `PascalCase` (`HeroPortraitPanel.tsx`)
- Utils/hooks: `camelCase` (`hero-utils.ts`, `useFilterParams.ts`)
